io.multimap

Class Callables.LessThan

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.multimap.Callables.LessThan
  • Enclosing class:
    Callables

    public abstract static class Callables.LessThan
extends Object
    A callable that is applied to two ByteBuffer's returning a boolean that tells if the left operand is less than the right operand. Objects implementing this interface are typically used by sorting algorithms.
    See Also:
    Map.optimize(java.nio.file.Path, java.nio.file.Path, Options)

      • call

        public boolean call(ByteBuffer a,
           ByteBuffer b)
        Determines whether a is less than b. This is a wrapper around callOnReadOnly(ByteBuffer, ByteBuffer) which marks the input as read-only.
        Returns:
        true if a is less than b, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        callOnReadOnly(ByteBuffer, ByteBuffer)

      • callOnReadOnly

        protected abstract boolean callOnReadOnly(ByteBuffer a,
                     ByteBuffer b)
        Determines whether a is less than b. The input is guaranteed to be read-only. Must be implemented in derived classes.
        Returns:
        true if a is less than b, false otherwise.
